Former Super Eagles captain Mikel Obi has tasked Nigeria’s track and field athletes to win gold in their respective events at the forthcoming Tokyo 2020 Olympic Games, The PUNCH reports. Mikel stated this during a dinner with some of the athletes who have qualified to represent Nigeria at the Games in Lagos on Sunday. Athletes present at the dinner were African long jump record holder Ese Brume, hurdler Tobi Amusan, sprinters Ushoritse Itsekiri, Grace Nwokocha, Favour Ofili and Amarachukwu Obi, throwers Oyesade Olatoye, Chukwuebuka Enekwechi, Chioma Onyekwere and Dotun Ogundeji. “I am happy to be in the midst of you guys,” said Mikel, who captained Nigeria’s U-23 team to a bronze medal finish in the football event at the 2016 Rio Olympics. “I know you are going to a major tournament which I have been to and I know what it takes to be there and to compete there and to try to win something for our great nation. “It’s my pleasure to be here to wish you guys all the best and hopefully, you will bring back gold medals from the Olympics. So, when you guys come back, we will celebrate with you, cheer with you.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com